Friends and family of brutally murdered Tshegofatso Pule said their final farewells to her on Thursday. An hour-long procession was held in Meadowlands, Soweto, and Pule was buried at the Roodepoort cemetery in the area. The 28-year-old's body was found in Durban Deep on Monday, hanging from a tree with a stab wound. She was eight months pregnant. Members of the police and military monitored the funeral, keeping an eye out for contraventions of the Covid-19 regulations. Many South Africans have protested against Pule's death, which has become yet another  in the country's ever-rising cases of gender-based violence. At the time of the funeral no arrests had been made.